UN Secretary-General Ban Arrives in Nigeria for Talks With Officials

-- B y   D u l u e   M b a c h u
-- 
2011-05-22T16:13:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-22/un-secretary-general-ban-arrives-in-nigeria-for-talks-with-officials.html
United Nations Secretary Ban Ki-moon
arrived in  Nigeria  today for a two-day visit to discuss regional
peace, health and sanitation issues with the country’s
officials.  Ban was received at the airport in the capital, Abuja, by
Nigerian Foreign Minister Odein Ajumogobia. He arrived from
Ivory Coast, where he attended the inauguration of Alassane
Ouattara as president yesterday and from Nigeria will travel to
Ethiopia and France, according to a statement on the UN website.  During his visit Ban will meet with President  Goodluck
Jonathan , head of the electoral agency and governors of the
country’s 36 states, according to an official program released
by the UN office in Nigeria.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net  